---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'
---

<Layout 
  title="Zero to Ship - Your Builder Journey" 
  description="A comprehensive roadmap for designers, PMs, and complete beginners ready to build and ship their own products. No BS, just practical steps to get you from idea to live product."
>
  <article class="learning-path">
    <header class="hero">
      <h1>Zero to Ship</h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">The No-BS Learning Path for Future Builders</p>
      <p class="hero-description">
        Whether you're a designer tired of hearing "not feasible," a PM wanting to prototype faster, 
        or someone with zero coding experience but big ideas‚Äîthis is your roadmap from complete beginner 
        to confident builder who ships real products.
      </p>
      
      <div class="quick-start">
        <h3>Find Your Starting Point:</h3>
        <div class="entry-points">
          <a href="#chapter-1" class="entry-point beginner">
            <strong>Complete Beginner</strong>
            <span>Never touched code</span>
          </a>
          <a href="#chapter-2" class="entry-point designer">
            <strong>Designer/Creative</strong>
            <span>Design tools expert</span>
          </a>
          <a href="#chapter-3" class="entry-point pm">
            <strong>PM/Strategist</strong>
            <span>Product-minded</span>
          </a>
          <a href="#chapter-4" class="entry-point technical">
            <strong>Some Technical</strong>
            <span>Basic HTML/CSS</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section class="progress-system">
      <h2>How This Works</h2>
      <div class="system-grid">
        <div class="system-item">
          <div class="icon">üìö</div>
          <h4>Chapter-Based Learning</h4>
          <p>5 progressive chapters that build on each other. Each chapter has clear skills, projects, and milestones.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="system-item">
          <div class="icon">üéØ</div>
          <h4>Build Real Things</h4>
          <p>Every chapter ends with shipping something live. No tutorial hell‚Äîyou'll have real products in your portfolio.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="system-item">
          <div class="icon">‚úÖ</div>
          <h4>Self-Paced Milestones</h4>
          <p>Clear "you're ready for next" checkpoints. No arbitrary timelines‚Äîmove when you're truly ready.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="system-item">
          <div class="icon">üèÜ</div>
          <h4>Portfolio Progression</h4>
          <p>Each project builds your public portfolio. By Chapter 5, you'll have 5 live products to show.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Chapter 1: Foundation -->
    <section id="chapter-1" class="chapter">
      <div class="chapter-header">
        <div class="chapter-meta">
          <span class="chapter-number">Chapter 1</span>
          <span class="chapter-theme">Foundation</span>
          <span class="time-estimate">2-4 weeks</span>
        </div>
        <h2>Get Your Hands Dirty</h2>
        <p class="chapter-description">
          Stop reading about coding and start doing it. This chapter gets you from "I don't know where to start" 
          to having your first live website on the internet.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="chapter-content">
        <div class="prerequisites">
          <h4>Prerequisites</h4>
          <p>Literally none. Just a computer and curiosity.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="skills-grid">
          <h4>Skills You'll Master</h4>
          <div class="skills">
            <div class="skill">
              <strong>Development Setup</strong>
              <p>VS Code, terminal basics, Git fundamentals</p>
            </div>
            <div class="skill">
              <strong>HTML/CSS Foundations</strong>
              <p>Structure, styling, responsive basics</p>
            </div>
            <div class="skill">
              <strong>Deployment Reality</strong>
              <p>Getting your work live on the internet</p>
            </div>
            <div class="skill">
              <strong>Learning How to Learn</strong>
              <p>Documentation, debugging, asking good questions</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="chapter-project">
          <h4>Chapter Project: Personal Landing Page</h4>
          <p>Build and deploy a simple personal landing page with:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Clean, professional design</li>
            <li>Responsive layout that works on all devices</li>
            <li>Contact form (using Netlify Forms or similar)</li>
            <li>Custom domain setup</li>
            <li>Basic SEO optimization</li>
          </ul>
          <p><strong>Real world result:</strong> A live website you can put on your resume/LinkedIn</p>
        </div>

        <div class="supporting-posts">
          <h4>Blog Posts for This Chapter</h4>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="/posts/hello-world">Hello World (From a Recovering Designer)</a></li>
            <li><em>Coming: "Terminal Terror: A Designer's Guide to Command Line"</em></li>
            <li><em>Coming: "Your First Deploy: From Local to Live in 10 Minutes"</em></li>
            <li><em>Coming: "Why Your First Website Should Be Embarrassingly Simple"</em></li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="milestone-check">
          <h4>You're Ready for Chapter 2 When...</h4>
          <ul class="checklist">
            <li>You can create a new HTML file and see it in the browser</li>
            <li>You've successfully deployed something live to the internet</li>
            <li>You can push changes to GitHub without crying</li>
            <li>You can inspect element and understand what you're seeing</li>
            <li>You have a basic understanding of CSS box model</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Chapter 2: Modern Tools -->
    <section id="chapter-2" class="chapter">
      <div class="chapter-header">
        <div class="chapter-meta">
          <span class="chapter-number">Chapter 2</span>
          <span class="chapter-theme">Modern Tools</span>
          <span class="time-estimate">3-6 weeks</span>
        </div>
        <h2>Level Up Your Toolkit</h2>
        <p class="chapter-description">
          Raw HTML/CSS is like designing in MS Paint. Time to discover the modern tools that make building 
          fast, fun, and maintainable. Hello, component-based thinking.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="chapter-content">
        <div class="prerequisites">
          <h4>Prerequisites</h4>
          <p>Completed Chapter 1 or equivalent: comfortable with HTML/CSS basics and deployment</p>
        </div>

        <div class="skills-grid">
          <h4>Skills You'll Master</h4>
          <div class="skills">
            <div class="skill">
              <strong>Modern CSS</strong>
              <p>Flexbox, Grid, CSS Variables, responsive design patterns</p>
            </div>
            <div class="skill">
              <strong>Static Site Generators</strong>
              <p>Astro, component thinking, markdown-driven content</p>
            </div>
            <div class="skill">
              <strong>Design Systems</strong>
              <p>Tokens, consistent spacing, typography scales</p>
            </div>
            <div class="skill">
              <strong>Content Management</strong>
              <p>Markdown, frontmatter, dynamic content generation</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="chapter-project">
          <h4>Chapter Project: Portfolio Blog</h4>
          <p>Build a modern blog/portfolio site with:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Component-based architecture (using Astro)</li>
            <li>Dynamic content from markdown files</li>
            <li>Consistent design system with CSS tokens</li>
            <li>Tag-based organization</li>
            <li>RSS feed and basic SEO</li>
          </ul>
          <p><strong>Real world result:</strong> A professional portfolio that you can easily maintain and expand</p>
        </div>

        <div class="supporting-posts">
          <h4>Blog Posts for This Chapter</h4>
          <ul>
            <li><em>Coming: "Component Thinking for Non-Developers"</em></li>
            <li><em>Coming: "Design Systems That Actually Work (No Figma Required)"</em></li>
            <li><em>Coming: "Why I Chose Astro (And You Might Too)"</em></li>
            <li><em>Coming: "CSS Grid vs Flexbox: The Real-World Decision Tree"</em></li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="milestone-check">
          <h4>You're Ready for Chapter 3 When...</h4>
          <ul class="checklist">
            <li>You can create reusable components in Astro</li>
            <li>You understand CSS Grid and Flexbox well enough to choose between them</li>
            <li>You can set up a new static site project from scratch</li>
            <li>You're comfortable with markdown and frontmatter</li>
            <li>You can implement a design system using CSS custom properties</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Chapter 3: Interactive & Dynamic -->
    <section id="chapter-3" class="chapter">
      <div class="chapter-header">
        <div class="chapter-meta">
          <span class="chapter-number">Chapter 3</span>
          <span class="chapter-theme">Interactive</span>
          <span class="time-estimate">4-8 weeks</span>
        </div>
        <h2>Make It Interactive</h2>
        <p class="chapter-description">
          Static sites are great, but the web is interactive. Time to add JavaScript, handle user input, 
          work with APIs, and build things that respond to user actions.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="chapter-content">
        <div class="prerequisites">
          <h4>Prerequisites</h4>
          <p>Completed Chapter 2 or equivalent: comfortable with modern CSS and static site generation</p>
        </div>

        <div class="skills-grid">
          <h4>Skills You'll Master</h4>
          <div class="skills">
            <div class="skill">
              <strong>JavaScript Fundamentals</strong>
              <p>DOM manipulation, event handling, async programming</p>
            </div>
            <div class="skill">
              <strong>API Integration</strong>
              <p>Fetch data, handle responses, work with third-party services</p>
            </div>
            <div class="skill">
              <strong>Form Handling</strong>
              <p>Validation, submission, user feedback</p>
            </div>
            <div class="skill">
              <strong>State Management</strong>
              <p>Managing application state, local storage, progressive enhancement</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="chapter-project">
          <h4>Chapter Project: Interactive Web App</h4>
          <p>Build a functional web application with:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>User authentication (Auth0 or similar)</li>
            <li>Data persistence (localStorage or simple database)</li>
            <li>API integration (weather, news, or your choice)</li>
            <li>Interactive UI components</li>
            <li>Progressive enhancement (works without JS)</li>
          </ul>
          <p><strong>Real world result:</strong> A functional web app that solves a real problem</p>
        </div>

        <div class="supporting-posts">
          <h4>Blog Posts for This Chapter</h4>
          <ul>
            <li><em>Coming: "JavaScript for People Who Hate JavaScript"</em></li>
            <li><em>Coming: "Your First API Call (And What to Do When It Breaks)"</em></li>
            <li><em>Coming: "Authentication Without Tears: Auth0 Setup"</em></li>
            <li><em>Coming: "Progressive Enhancement: Building for Everyone"</em></li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="milestone-check">
          <h4>You're Ready for Chapter 4 When...</h4>
          <ul class="checklist">
            <li>You can handle user input and form submissions</li>
            <li>You've successfully integrated with at least one third-party API</li>
            <li>You understand async/await and can handle promises</li>
            <li>You can add interactive features without breaking accessibility</li>
            <li>You've built something that stores and retrieves user data</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Chapter 4: Full Stack Thinking -->
    <section id="chapter-4" class="chapter">
      <div class="chapter-header">
        <div class="chapter-meta">
          <span class="chapter-number">Chapter 4</span>
          <span class="chapter-theme">Full Stack</span>
          <span class="time-estimate">6-10 weeks</span>
        </div>
        <h2>Think Like a Product</h2>
        <p class="chapter-description">
          Time to connect the dots. Databases, server-side logic, user management, payments. 
          Everything you need to build complete digital products that can scale.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="chapter-content">
        <div class="prerequisites">
          <h4>Prerequisites</h4>
          <p>Completed Chapter 3 or equivalent: comfortable with JavaScript, APIs, and interactive web apps</p>
        </div>

        <div class="skills-grid">
          <h4>Skills You'll Master</h4>
          <div class="skills">
            <div class="skill">
              <strong>Database Fundamentals</strong>
              <p>SQL basics, data modeling, relationships</p>
            </div>
            <div class="skill">
              <strong>Server-Side Logic</strong>
              <p>API endpoints, middleware, authentication</p>
            </div>
            <div class="skill">
              <strong>Payment Integration</strong>
              <p>Stripe setup, handling transactions, webhooks</p>
            </div>
            <div class="skill">
              <strong>Deployment & Scaling</strong>
              <p>Database hosting, environment variables, monitoring</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="chapter-project">
          <h4>Chapter Project: SaaS MVP</h4>
          <p>Build a complete SaaS application with:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>User registration and subscription management</li>
            <li>Database-driven features</li>
            <li>Payment processing with Stripe</li>
            <li>Admin dashboard</li>
            <li>Production deployment with monitoring</li>
          </ul>
          <p><strong>Real world result:</strong> A real business you could actually run and scale</p>
        </div>

        <div class="supporting-posts">
          <h4>Blog Posts for This Chapter</h4>
          <ul>
            <li><em>Coming: "Database Design for Non-Database People"</em></li>
            <li><em>Coming: "Stripe Integration: Taking Money on the Internet"</em></li>
            <li><em>Coming: "From Side Project to SaaS: The Minimum Viable Stack"</em></li>
            <li><em>Coming: "Production-Ready: Monitoring, Backups, and Sleep"</em></li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="milestone-check">
          <h4>You're Ready for Chapter 5 When...</h4>
          <ul class="checklist">
            <li>You can design and implement a database schema</li>
            <li>You've successfully processed real payments</li>
            <li>You can deploy full-stack applications to production</li>
            <li>You understand basic security principles and implement them</li>
            <li>You have a complete SaaS MVP that's actually live</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Chapter 5: Ship & Scale -->
    <section id="chapter-5" class="chapter">
      <div class="chapter-header">
        <div class="chapter-meta">
          <span class="chapter-number">Chapter 5</span>
          <span class="chapter-theme">Ship & Scale</span>
          <span class="time-estimate">Ongoing</span>
        </div>
        <h2>Build a Sustainable Business</h2>
        <p class="chapter-description">
          You're no longer a beginner. Now it's about building sustainable products, managing technical debt, 
          growing your skills, and maybe even building a business around your newfound abilities.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="chapter-content">
        <div class="prerequisites">
          <h4>Prerequisites</h4>
          <p>Completed Chapter 4 or equivalent: built and deployed a complete full-stack application</p>
        </div>

        <div class="skills-grid">
          <h4>Skills You'll Master</h4>
          <div class="skills">
            <div class="skill">
              <strong>Product Strategy</strong>
              <p>User research, feature prioritization, growth metrics</p>
            </div>
            <div class="skill">
              <strong>Code Quality</strong>
              <p>Testing, refactoring, documentation, maintainable architecture</p>
            </div>
            <div class="skill">
              <strong>Business Operations</strong>
              <p>Customer support, analytics, legal basics, scaling infrastructure</p>
            </div>
            <div class="skill">
              <strong>Continuous Learning</strong>
              <p>Staying current, learning new technologies, building community</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="chapter-project">
          <h4>Chapter Project: Scalable Product Business</h4>
          <p>Take your skills and build something sustainable:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Identify and validate a real market opportunity</li>
            <li>Build and launch a complete product</li>
            <li>Implement proper analytics and user feedback systems</li>
            <li>Scale to handle real user load</li>
            <li>Build systems for sustainable growth</li>
          </ul>
          <p><strong>Real world result:</strong> Either a profitable side business or the skills to command senior developer roles</p>
        </div>

        <div class="supporting-posts">
          <h4>Blog Posts for This Chapter</h4>
          <ul>
            <li><em>Coming: "From Builder to Business Owner: The Transition"</em></li>
            <li><em>Coming: "Technical Debt: When to Refactor, When to Rebuild"</em></li>
            <li><em>Coming: "Building in Public: Lessons from 1 Year of Shipping"</em></li>
            <li><em>Coming: "The Senior Developer Mindset (Without the Years)"</em></li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="milestone-check">
          <h4>You've Completed Zero to Ship When...</h4>
          <ul class="checklist">
            <li>You have 5+ live products in your portfolio</li>
            <li>You can confidently build full-stack applications from scratch</li>
            <li>You have real users using something you built</li>
            <li>You can debug complex issues and implement new features independently</li>
            <li>You're helping others learn (the ultimate test of mastery)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Community & Support -->
    <section class="community">
      <h2>Community & Progress Tracking</h2>
      
      <div class="community-features">
        <div class="feature">
          <h4>üéØ Progress Tracking</h4>
          <p>Use our simple GitHub template to track your journey. Fork the repo, check off milestones, and showcase your projects.</p>
          <a href="#" class="cta-button">Get Progress Template</a>
        </div>
        
        <div class="feature">
          <h4>ü§ù Learning Community</h4>
          <p>Join the discussion on GitHub Discussions. Share your projects, ask questions, and help others on their journey.</p>
          <a href="#" class="cta-button">Join Community</a>
        </div>
        
        <div class="feature">
          <h4>üìà Public Progress</h4>
          <p>Build in public. Share your chapter projects on Twitter/LinkedIn with #ZeroToShip. Get feedback and inspire others.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="feature">
          <h4>üèÜ Milestone Celebrations</h4>
          <p>Completed a chapter? Share it! We'll retweet/share your wins and help you build your reputation as a builder.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="realistic-expectations">
        <h3>Realistic Expectations</h3>
        <div class="expectations-grid">
          <div class="expectation">
            <strong>Time Investment</strong>
            <p>5-10 hours per week minimum. This isn't a 30-day challenge‚Äîit's a skill for life. Quality over speed.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="expectation">
            <strong>Total Timeline</strong>
            <p>6-18 months to complete all chapters, depending on your starting point and time commitment. Rushing helps no one.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="expectation">
            <strong>Cost</strong>
            <p>$0-50/month in tools and hosting. Learning to build shouldn't break the bank. We'll show you the free alternatives.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="expectation">
            <strong>Success Rate</strong>
            <p>High‚Äîif you complete Chapter 1. Most people quit before shipping their first project. Don't be most people.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Getting Started -->
    <section class="get-started">
      <h2>Ready to Start Building?</h2>
      <p>Pick your entry point and begin your journey from zero to ship. No more excuses, no more "someday"‚Äîtoday is the day you start building.</p>
      
      <div class="start-buttons">
        <a href="#chapter-1" class="start-button primary">Start Chapter 1: Foundation</a>
        <a href="/subscribe" class="start-button secondary">Get Updates on New Chapters</a>
      </div>
      
      <p class="start-note">
        <strong>Pro tip:</strong> Even if you think you can skip ahead, spend 1 week on Chapter 1. 
        The foundation habits you build here will make everything else easier.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .learning-path {
    max-width: var(--content-max-width);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 var(--page-padding);
  }

  /* Hero Section */
  .hero {
    text-align: center;
    padding: calc(var(--space-10) + var(--space-8)) 0 var(--space-8);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-neutral-20);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
  }

  .hero h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif-display);
    font-size: var(--font-size-3xl);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-semibold);
    line-height: var(--line-height-tight);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
  }

  .hero-subtitle {
    font-family: var(--font-sans-geometric);
    font-size: var(--font-size-large);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-medium);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: var(--letter-spacing-wide);
    color: var(--color-accent-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
  }

  .hero-description {
    font-size: var(--font-size-large);
    line-height: var(--line-height-relaxed);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto var(--space-8) auto;
  }

  .quick-start h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-sans-geometric);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: var(--letter-spacing-wide);
    font-size: var(--font-size-small);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .entry-points {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-4);
    margin-top: var(--space-5);
  }

  .entry-point {
    display: block;
    padding: var(--space-4);
    border: 2px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    text-decoration: none;
    text-align: center;
    transition: all var(--transition-normal);
  }

  .entry-point:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-accent-primary);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .entry-point strong {
    display: block;
    font-size: var(--font-size-base);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-1);
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
  }

  .entry-point span {
    font-size: var(--font-size-small);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }

  /* Progress System */
  .progress-system {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-9);
    padding: var(--space-7) 0;
  }

  .progress-system h2 {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }

  .system-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-6);
  }

  .system-item {
    text-align: center;
  }

  .system-item .icon {
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  .system-item h4 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    font-size: var(--font-size-large);
  }

  /* Chapter Styles */
  .chapter {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-9);
    padding: var(--space-7) 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .chapter-header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-7);
  }

  .chapter-meta {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    font-family: var(--font-sans-geometric);
    font-size: var(--font-size-small);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: var(--letter-spacing-wide);
  }

  .chapter-number {
    color: var(--color-accent-primary);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold);
  }

  .chapter-theme {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }

  .time-estimate {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .chapter h2 {
    font-size: var(--font-size-3xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .chapter-description {
    font-size: var(--font-size-large);
    line-height: var(--line-height-relaxed);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    max-width: 600px;
  }

  .chapter-content {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-7);
  }

  /* Chapter Content Sections */
  .prerequisites,
  .chapter-project,
  .supporting-posts,
  .milestone-check {
    padding: var(--space-5);
    background: var(--color-bg-alt);
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

  .prerequisites h4,
  .chapter-project h4,
